[{"sha":"038d5f969a883773cbf14cd152167754c9eaa231","author":{"email":"746aced590a184ef4169166e753f7c211e32e5fc@tensorflow.org","name":"A. Unique TensorFlower"},"message":"Rebound dim size for the dynamic dimension in Where xla op kernel

tf.repeat generates Where op with compile constant input. This should be constant folded so that the use of the output in Gather op generates correct shaped output. Which, then later goes through the Reshape op.

The relevant IR looks something like this,

%gather_indices = tf.Where(%mask)
%elements = tf.GatherV2(input, %gather_indices)
%result = tf.Reshape(%elements, %shape)

Added a hyperparameter beta in swish activation function.

As described in (https://arxiv.org/abs/1710.05941) swish consists of a beta hyperparamter that is inputted in the sigmoid activation function. Implemented to paramter beta with default value of 1.0 in order to replicate the same behavior as current if no value is provided.
